{
  "texts": [
    "When deploying new technologies like LLMs, it is crucial to consider potential harms stemming from their inherent characteristics (detailed in Section 3.1.4 and Section 3.2.5).",
    "These include the risk of generating and spreading misinformation (14), and negative impacts that can arise from inappropriate humanization or a lack of operational robustness in sensitive applications (49, 55).",
    "Beyond privacy breaches and bias, using sentiment analysis in public health carries other potential harms.",
    "Revealing sensitive information could cause reputational damage or psychological distress (11).",
    "Misinterpreting or misusing findings can lead to flawed decisions (65)."
  ]
}